## Routes

- `GET /` – simple text health check
- `GET /echo/{name}` – path parameter echo
- `GET /headers` – prints the incoming `user-agent`
- `GET /stream` – emits a short streamed response body
- `POST /echo` – echoes JSON payloads
- `GET|POST /proxy/{*rest}` – forwards requests to `API_BASE_URL`, falling back to a 501 when the active adapter does not expose a proxy client

